Class Team

  • java.lang.Object
    • Team

  • public class Team
extends java.lang.Object
    Team class holds all of the TeamMembers in a team and provides functionalities for the team. This class keeps track of how many member are in each instance at all times. Team class allows for addition of new members and as many members as wanted (as much as device storage allows). Also allows for removal of members.
    Author:
    Tin Fung, Rizwan Chowdhury

      • remove

        public boolean remove(TeamMember m)
        Accepts a TeamMember as an argument and removes that member from the team, also reduces number of member by 1. Finds the TeamMember in the team array and removes it.
        Parameters:
        m - TeamMember object to be removed from the team.
        Returns:
        true if the removal was successful, false if member was not in the team.
